11
00:00:35,840 --> 00:00:37,160
Yongle Casino?

12
00:00:38,920 --> 00:00:39,880
Qin Zhiyuan,

13
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:41,120
35 years old,

14
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:43,640
used to work as a tenant farmer in the Li's Estate.

15
00:00:43,640 --> 00:00:44,500
He's literate.

16
00:00:44,560 --> 00:00:46,960
He's applying for the position of bailiff.

17
00:00:47,520 --> 00:00:48,520
Ms. Zhang,

18
00:00:48,560 --> 00:00:49,560
28 years old,

19
00:00:49,600 --> 00:00:52,240
has never worked outside before as she's a woman.

20
00:00:52,240 --> 00:00:54,900
She's applying for the position of wine brewer.

21
00:01:00,120 --> 00:01:01,800
Since you're literate and have studied at school before,

22
00:01:01,800 --> 00:01:04,000
then I'll ask you a question to test you.

23
00:01:04,120 --> 00:01:06,180
Imagine that there are 500 combs now.

24
00:01:06,200 --> 00:01:08,260
You need to sell them all to the monks.

25
00:01:08,600 --> 00:01:09,930
What are you going to do?

26
00:01:11,080 --> 00:01:13,880
Young Madam, have you asked a wrong test question?

27
00:01:16,240 --> 00:01:18,920
I'll give you some time to think about it carefully.

28
00:01:18,920 --> 00:01:21,050
Think it through before you answer me.

29
00:01:28,800 --> 00:01:29,930
Fourth Young Madam,

30
00:01:30,640 --> 00:01:33,039
monks don't need combs.

31
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:34,240
However,

32
00:01:34,240 --> 00:01:37,039
the guests who come to offer incense may need them.

33
00:01:37,360 --> 00:01:40,440
We can ask the temple to engrave the sutra on the comb

34
00:01:40,840 --> 00:01:41,759
and name it

35
00:01:42,190 --> 00:01:45,080
"Peace Comb", "Virtues Accumulation Comb" or "Good Deeds Comb".

36
00:01:45,080 --> 00:01:48,120
They can give the combs to those guests who have donated money to the temple.

37
00:01:48,120 --> 00:01:49,440
It'll not only promote the ideas of Buddhism,

38
00:01:49,440 --> 00:01:50,800
but it'll also be a way to thank the people for their kindness.

39
00:01:50,800 --> 00:01:51,400
Very good.

40
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:54,440
Literate men are supposed to be quick-witted.

41
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:56,400
You are hired.

42
00:01:57,400 --> 00:01:59,130
Thank you, Fourth Young Madam.

43
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:01,560
I really don't understand such a test question

44
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:02,360
you've asked.

45
00:02:02,520 --> 00:02:03,400
I'm leaving first.

46
00:02:03,400 --> 00:02:04,000
Wait.

47
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:06,360
You're

48
00:02:06,360 --> 00:02:07,400
hired, too.

49
00:02:09,479 --> 00:02:10,280
Young Madam.

50
00:02:10,280 --> 00:02:11,740
She didn't even say a word.

51
00:02:12,480 --> 00:02:13,840
As soon as Ms. Zhang came in,

52
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:16,000
I smelled the fragrance of osmanthus.

53
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:18,440
If she hadn't dealt with wine for many years,

54
00:02:18,440 --> 00:02:20,640
